    {
      "date_stolen": null,
      "description": "White with tritone blue design and lettering. Has a black cargo rack on the back. Tires are somewhere between 20 and 24 inches. Built in battery.\r\nFound over Christmas/winter break, December 2025. Was \"abandoned\" along centre Ave and was lying unlocked and unattended in the grass between the road and the bike trail on the west side of Centre. After looking around and waiting 45 minutes or so, I decided to move it against the fence and put a note on it. The note basically called for the attention of the owner to claim the bike or risk forfeiture. I walked by the bike daily for 5 days, making sure it was still visible from the road and trail and that my note with phone number were still attached. On day 5, I was so excited that it was still there and it was like a Christmas present from the universe!!\r\nAlthough the students aren't all back from their vacations, im pretty sure that it is still abandoned or unclaimed as there is no CSU registration sticker on it so must have had a non-student owner.\r\nAnyway, it is now day 7 and I have brought the bike home to register and officially adopt !! :) yay",
      "frame_colors": [
        "White",
        "Blue"
      ],
      "frame_model": "XP foldable",
